        "1760": {
          "vnum": 1760,
          "name": "On the Rooftops",
          "description": "You frighten pigeons from their perches as you invade the rooftops. Some places are white with their stool. From a window below you hear singing, and from another the sounds of clinking glassware. Rooftops to the west and south allow you to continue your aerial passage.",
